source: Embed related entities in the response. For example: use a query string like ?include=comments.author to include all the entities referenced by comments and all the entities referenced by author on those entities!. @link.
OpenAPI support for the JSON:API module.
Pagination can be a deceptively complex topic. It's easy to fall into traps and not follow best-practices. @link.
The JSON:API module allows you to sort collections based on properties in the resource or in nested resources. @link.
The JSON:API module exposes entity revisions as resource versions. @link.
The JSON:API module has some of the most robust and feature-rich filtering features around. All of that power comes with a bit of a learning curve though. @link.
